# 04 — Conversion (Top Priority)

> Conversion outranks aesthetics in every tie. The page exists to turn visitors into registrants.

## Primary Conversion Goal
A completed registration (Name, Email, Phone, College/Company, Experience Level) for **₹109**. Every section must push toward, or remove friction from, this single action.

## CTA System
- **Primary CTA** label: `Reserve My Seat` / `Reserve My Seat for ₹109`. Style: `--primary` fill, white text, soft glow, magnetic hover. There is exactly ONE primary visual treatment site-wide.
- **Secondary CTA**: `Watch Demo` — low-emphasis ghost/text button. Never competes with primary.
- CTAs must be **persistently reachable**: hero CTA, sticky form on desktop (≥1024px), and a sticky bottom CTA bar on mobile that reveals after the hero scrolls out.
- Every CTA states or implies the price and the action. No vague "Learn more" as a primary path.

## Friction Reduction
- Single-column form, 5 fields max, no account creation, no email verification gate before checkout.
- Inline validation, no surprise required-field errors after submit.
- Show price (`₹109`) adjacent to every registration CTA — never make users hunt for cost.
- Reduce cognitive load: one decision per screen. Don't ask the user to compare plans (there is one offer).

## Urgency & Scarcity (real, never fake)
- **Countdown timer** to June 7, 2026 2:00 PM IST — in hero and final CTA.
- **Seats Remaining** indicator — must be backed by a real/config-driven number, not random JS. If decrementing, base it on actual data or a documented controlled value; never invent live fake counts.
- Calm urgency language (see brand voice). No blinking red, no fake "3 people viewing".

## Trust Architecture (place before the ask)
- Clear what-you-get (Section 3 "What You Will Build").
- Concrete agenda (Section 5) so the buyer knows exactly what 3 hours delivers.
- Real instructor authority (Section 6) and authentic testimonials (Section 7) immediately before/around the form.
- Price transparency + "Live Online" + duration repeated near CTAs.

## Persuasion Architecture (section order = funnel)
Hook (hero) → Problem/Shift (the AI shift) → Tangible outcomes (what you'll build) → Proof of mechanism (live workflow) → Specifics (agenda) → Credibility (instructor) → Social proof (testimonials) → Action (registration) → Objection handling (FAQ) → Final urgency close.

## Objection Handling
FAQ must directly answer the real blockers: "Do I need coding?" (No), "Is it recorded?", "What do I need to attend?", "Refunds?", "Who is this for?". Each FAQ removes a reason not to buy.

## Measurement Hooks (build-time requirement)
Instrument: hero CTA click, secondary CTA click, form field focus (first interaction), form submit, registration success, feedback submit, countdown-expiry view. Use a single typed analytics wrapper (`track(event, props)`). No PII in event props.

## CRO Don'ts
No multiple competing primary CTAs, no carousel that hides value, no auto-playing audio, no popups that block the offer, no dark patterns. Scarcity must be honest.
